Rescaling the Features¶

It is extremely important to rescale the variables so that they have a comparable scale. There are twocoon ways of rescaling

Normalisation (min-max scaling) and standardisation (mean-o, sigma-1) Let's try normalisation

In [41]:
#defining a normalisation function 
def normalize (x): 
    return ( (x-np.mean(x))/ (max(x) - min(x)))
                                            
                                              
# applying normalize ( ) to all columns 
data = data.apply(normalize)

Building model using sklearn¶

In [45]:
# Importing RFE and LinearRegression
from sklearn.feature_selection import RFE
from sklearn.linear_model import LinearRegression

In [110]:
def checkVIF(X):
    vif = pd.DataFrame()
    vif['Features'] = X.columns
    vif['VIF'] = [variance_inflation_factor(X.values, i) for i in range(X.shape[1])]
    vif['VIF'] = round(vif['VIF'], 2)
    vif = vif.sort_values(by = "VIF", ascending = False)
    return(vif)
